<P>THE HISTORY OF The Late Revolution <HI>OF THE</HI> EMPIRE OF THE <HI>GREAT MOGOL:</HI> Together with the mo&s;t con&s;iderable Pa&s;&s;ages for 5 years following in that Empire.</P>
<P><HI>To which is added,</HI> A LETTER to the Lord <HI>COLBERT,</HI> touching the Extent of <HI>Indo&s;tan;</HI> the Circu|lation of the Gold and Silver of the World, to di&s;charge it &s;elf there; as al&s;o the <HI>Riches, Forces,</HI> and <HI>Ju&s;tice</HI> of the &s;ame: And the Prin|cipal Cau&s;e of the Decay of the States of <HI>A&s;ia.</HI></P>
<P><HI>By Mon&s;^r</HI> F. BERNIER, Phy&s;itian of the Faculty of <HI>Montpelier.</HI></P>
<P>Engli&s;h'd out of French.</P>
<P>THE SECOND EDITION.</P>
<P><HI>LONDON</HI> Printed, and Sold by <HI>M. Pitt</HI> at the <HI>Angel,</HI> and <HI>S. Miller</HI> at the <HI>Star,</HI> in St. <HI>Paul's Church yard;</HI> and <HI>J. Starkey</HI> at the <HI>Miter</HI> near <HI>Temple-Bar.</HI> 1676.</P>
<PB REF="2">
